<br>
For Naggy, there are only a couple drops that matter: satchel is the most valuable in terms of time used.  A monk will use it forever (everyone else will sell it to a monk and buy two tinks).  CoF is most valuable in terms of utility over time; most will use it well past 60 and it's a major haste upgrade.  After that, it's all trade-bait or short-term upgrades with the possible exception of the paladin epic part.  Most Pals bank their epics and never use them, but they all want them very badly for some reason (and they all swear to use them forever). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderating inconsistently<br>since Jun 2002</span><br>  Posts: 1376<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/30/02 1:57:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1475.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Sheesh</span><hr size=1> Just a note on Nag loot,<br>
<br>
Selo's drums are like 3rd best in the game.  Most bards will use through 60.<br>
<br>
Crown of King Tranixx (it's fire giant loot, but might as well include it) is a good helmet.  I won mine on a Nag raid half a year ago, and I still wear it.<br>
<br>
Red Dragonscale (is used in epics, of course, so it'll always be valuable).<br>
